  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Stores may purchase large quantities of devices from a supplier that require refurbishment before they are ready to sell. RepairQ allows users to create a custom inventory status for these items, so they can be tracked in the system. These items can be brought into inventory via the Purchase Order (PO) process and received under the new, custom status. After receiving these items, you can use filters to sort by the new status and utilize the Bulk-Edit feature to place these items on Refurb Tickets. This article will demonstrate our recommendation for this workflow.</p><h3 id=\"PurchaseOrders:ReceivingRefurbItemsinBulk-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932427416/Purchase+Order+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932427416\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Purchase Order Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932624055/Inventory+Status+Overview\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932624055\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Inventory Status - What Does It Mean?</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932525726/Automated+Notifications+Inventory+Status+Changes\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932525726\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Automated Notifications: Inventory Status Changes</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1930494541/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"PurchaseOrders:ReceivingRefurbItemsinBulk-CreateaNewInventoryStatustoReceiveItemsforRefurbishment\">Create a New Inventory Status to Receive Items for Refurbishment</h2><p>Inventory statuses that are created are considered <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932624055/Inventory+Status+Overview\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932624055\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Transitional Inventory</a>. We recommend receiving items in this status so they are not accidentally added to a ticket.</p><p /><p>1. On the Navigation bar, go to <strong>Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Company</strong> <strong>Settings</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1930494541/Receive%20Bulk%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. On the Settings Overview page, the left column has settings sorted by category. Go to <strong>Catalog</strong> \u2192 <strong>Inventory</strong> <strong>Statuses</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"564\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1930494541/Receive%20Bulk%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3. On the Inventory Status page, click <strong>Add</strong> <strong>Inventory</strong> <strong>Status</strong> to create a new status. Name the status &quot;Received for Refurb&quot; or something similar and click <strong>Save</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"340\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1930494541/Bulk%20Refurb%201.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"PurchaseOrders:ReceivingRefurbItemsinBulk-ReceivingRefurbItemsonaPurchaseOrder(PO)\">Receiving Refurb Items on a Purchase Order (PO)</h2><p>1. If you have not already done so, <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932722231/Purchase+Order+Process+Creating+a+New+Purchase+Order\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932722231\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">create a Purchase Order</a> for the devices that you are bringing into inventory.</p><p /><p>2. Once the devices have been delivered, navigate to the Purchase Order and click <strong>Edit</strong> to begin receiving the items.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1930494541/Bulk%20Refurb%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>3. Receive each item in the PO by scanning or typing in the IMEI/serial of each item that you have received. <strong>Make sure that in the Status field, you select the new inventory status that you created earlier</strong> (in this example, the status is Received for Refurb). Continue the process by filling out the Condition and Carrier fields. Once finished, click <strong>Receive Items</strong> and reconcile the PO.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1930494541/Bulk%20Refurb%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p><strong>Note</strong>: You can also set up an automation to notify a staff member when items have been placed in a specific inventory status. For more information, check out our article, <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932525726/Automated+Notifications+Inventory+Status+Changes\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932525726\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Automated Notifications: Inventory Status Changes</a>.</p><p /><h2 id=\"PurchaseOrders:ReceivingRefurbItemsinBulk-CreatingRefurbTicketsfortheReceivedItems\">Creating Refurb Tickets for the Received Items</h2><p>1. On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Inventory</strong> \u2192 <strong>Inventory</strong> <strong>Detail</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1930494541/Bulk%20Refurb%209.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>2. On the Inventory Detail page, filter the list by <strong>Status - Received for Refurb</strong> (the status that was created for this example), and click <strong>Apply</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1930494541/Bulk%20Refurb%204.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p><strong>Note</strong>: The list will display all items in that status. By default, results will only show for the last 90 days. You may need to set the Date Range filter for All Time if there are items that have aged past that time period.</p><p /><p>3. You can use the <a class=\"createlink\" href=\"/wiki/pages/createpage.action?spaceKey=SCD&amp;title=Inventory%20Management%3A%20Editing%20Inventory%20Attributes&amp;linkCreation=true&amp;fromPageId=1930494541\">Bulk Edit feature</a> to select multiple devices and create Refurbish Tickets for each device. Select the device(s) you want to create Refurb tickets for, click the <strong>Edit Selected button</strong>, and click <strong>Refurb</strong> <strong>Selected</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1930494541/Bulk%20Refurb%205.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"224\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1930494541/Bulk%20Refurb%206.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>4. A &quot;Bulk Refurb&quot; pop-up will appear. Select the location assignment for the refurb tickets, and the assignee (if applicable), and add Diagnostic notes. When you have made your selections, click <strong>Refurb</strong> <strong>Items</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1930494541/Bulk%20Refurb%207.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>5. To locate the Refurb tickets, navigate to the Ticket Queue. The new tickets will appear at the bottom of the page. If you click the Date column, you can sort by date created and bring the tickets to the top of the Ticket List.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1930494541/Bulk%20Refurb%208.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.18.X</p>",
